``` ::: ::: ```{=html} ``` Note: The plot depicts the relationship between the access (higher values - fairer access) to state subsidies for campaigning, publication of financial accounts (higher values - more transparency), on the one hand, and the abuse of state resources (higher values - more abuse), on the other hand. Additionally, it breaks down this relationship by the level of democratic development (colour) and GDP per capita (larger points - higher GDP). Overall, democracy and wealth are associated with fairer access to subsidies and more transparency of financial accounts than partly free and non-free regimes. Data reflects expert opinions. Use the mouse to rotate/spin, zoom in, and hover over the plot for more details. Data source: [@garnett2022] ::: {#references} :::
